@page "/privacy"
@layout PublicLayout

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy — Nornis</PageTitle>

<article class="nornis-public-page">
    <div class="nornis-eyebrow">Privacy Policy</div>
    <h1>Your campaign is yours</h1>
    <p class="nornis-public-updated">Last updated: July 2026</p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <p>
        Nornis stores what you give it: campaign names, sources (session notes, journals,
        transcripts, links), and the artifacts, facts, and storylines derived from them. Your
        account carries only what sign-in requires — a username, an email address, and the
        identifier from our sign-in provider. We do not store passwords.
    </p>

    <h2>How AI processing works</h2>
    <p>
        When you submit a source for extraction or ask the Loremaster a question, the relevant
        campaign content is sent to our AI provider (Azure OpenAI) to generate the response. That
        content is not used to train AI models. We record token counts, costs, and timing for
        each AI operation — visible to you on your campaign's Costs page — but we do not log
        prompt content.
    </p>

    <h2>Visibility inside a campaign</h2>
    <p>
        Campaign content is visible only to that campaign's members, according to the visibility
        each item carries: private items to their creator, GM-only items to GMs, party-visible
        items to everyone in the campaign. There is no public or anonymous access to campaign
        content.
    </p>

    <h2>What we don't do</h2>
    <p>
        We don't sell your data. We don't share campaign content with third parties beyond the
        infrastructure needed to run the service (hosting, database, and AI processing). We
        don't use your campaign content for advertising or model training.
    </p>

    <h2>Deletion</h2>
    <p>
        Deleting a source, artifact, or campaign removes it from the working record. If you want
        your account and all associated data removed, contact us and we'll do it.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about this policy: reach the maintainer through the project's repository.</p>
</article>
